THE SHELTERING SKY an utterly ridiculous performance, devoid of talent.1 You ought to have had the manuscript checked by a cultured Arab. Thanks all the same for sending me those books. I hope you don't mind this frank expression of my opinion.

Sincerely yours,





TO: JOHN FISCHER

CC, 1 p.





802 E. Seneca Street

Ithaca, N.Y.

9 May 1950

